CHANGELOG.md:529:- Tightened sw_sampler end-to-end JSON diagnostic coverage (frac-0116c): `SwSamplerEndToEndTests.test_sw_sampler_source_and_runtime_harness_round_trip_json_diagnostic` in `tests/test_sw_sampler.py` now asserts the round-tripped diagnostic carries exactly the canonical fourteen-name `defaults` set (`bufnum`, `amp`, `grain_size_ms`, `density`, `position`, `position_rate`, `pitch_transpose_semitones`, `pitch_jitter_semitones`, `attack_sec`, `release_sec`, `gate`, `out_bus`, `fx_bus`, `fx_send`) and exactly the canonical eight-stage `signal_chain` set (`grain_trigger`, `pitch_jitter`, `pitch_transpose`, `position_scrub`, `grain_buffer`, `envelope`, `dry_out`, `fx_send_out`) via set equality plus explicit length, lifting the round-tripped coverage from a six-of-fourteen / list-equality spot-check to exhaustive cardinality and content checks. The new assertions are additive — existing assertions and source/runtime behavior are unchanged — so they pass against the current code on first run; full validation (`pip install -e '.[dev]' && pytest tests/ -x && ruff check src/ tests/ && mypy src/`) remains clean (`4670 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean), startup identity anchors remain green (`11 passed`), and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
CHANGELOG.md:531:- Added the RED sw_sampler depth-marker gate (frac-0116a): `tests/test_test_sw_sampler_depth.py` now parses `tests/test_sw_sampler.py` and requires a machine-readable depth-2 declaration in the module docstring (`depth: 2` / `depth = 2`) or an equivalent top-level `DEPTH` constant. The marker itself is intentionally not added in this task, so `pytest tests/test_test_sw_sampler_depth.py::test_test_sw_sampler_declares_machine_readable_depth_two_marker -q` fails until the follow-up implementation supplies the marker. Existing frac-0116 sampler depth and end-to-end checks remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
CHANGELOG.md:533:- Added depth-2 sw_sampler end-to-end test coverage (frac-0116): `tests/test_sw_sampler.py` now includes `SwSamplerEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing `my-claw/tools/senseweave/synthesis/sw_sampler.scd` granular SynthDef source and the SC-side runtime harness `my-claw/supercollider/test_sw_sampler.scd` through one diagnostic lifecycle. The test extracts every documented SynthDef control default (`bufnum`, `amp`, `grain_size_ms=80.0`, `density=12.0`, `position`, `position_rate`, `pitch_transpose_semitones`, `pitch_jitter_semitones`, `attack_sec`, `release_sec`, `gate>=1`, `out_bus=0`, `fx_bus`, `fx_send=0.4`), verifies the integrated granular signal-chain order (`Impulse.kr` -> `TRand.kr` -> `.midiratio` -> `Sweep.ar`/`Phasor.ar` -> `GrainBuf.ar(... bufnum ...)` -> `EnvGen.kr(Env.asr, gate, doneAction: 2)` -> dry `Out.ar(out_bus, ...)` -> parallel `Out.ar(fx_bus, ...)` send) on a comment-stripped source, confirms the dry write to `out_bus` is not scaled by `fx_send` so the parallel-send architecture is preserved, inspects the SC-side runtime harness for source compile, 2-second render, non-silence, FFT spectral peak, gate=0 release tail, and known-content buffer allocation, and round-trips a JSON-safe diagnostic of the SynthDef name, source path, runtime-harness path, defaults, signal-chain stages, stage positions, and runtime checks through `json.dumps(..., sort_keys=True)`. `tests/test_test_sw_sampler_depth.py` pins the test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the named end-to-end class/method. Existing production behavior remains unchanged because the SCD source and SC-side harness already produced the required one-path output; startup identity anchors remain green (`11 passed`) and the full validation gate (`4669 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remains clean, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
CHANGELOG.md:539:- Added depth-2 sampler-effects end-to-end test coverage (frac-0113): `tests/test_sampler_effects.py` now includes `SamplerEffectsEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing `sw_sampler_fx` SuperCollider source and SC-side runtime harness through one diagnostic lifecycle. The test extracts bus/control defaults (`in_bus=16`, `out_bus=0`, delay/reverb/freeze/comb controls), verifies the ordered integrated FX chain (`In.ar` -> `DelayC.ar` -> `FreeVerb.ar` -> `PV_Freeze` -> `CombC.ar` -> `LPF.ar` -> `Out.ar`), confirms the runtime harness compiles `sampler_effects.scd`, toggles `freeze_amount`, exercises `comb_decay` / `comb_damping`, runs `runImpulseComb`, checks the 61.74 Hz comb target, and round-trips a JSON-safe diagnostic. `tests/test_test_sampler_effects_depth.py` pins the test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the named end-to-end class/method. Existing SuperCollider behavior remains unchanged because the source already produced the required one-path FX chain; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4663 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
CHANGELOG.md:647:- Added depth-2 cast-planner end-to-end test coverage (frac-0063): `tests/test_cast_planner.py` now ships a `TestCastPlannerEndToEnd` class that drives the existing public cast-planner surface (`select_cast_ids`, `assemble_cast`, plus the exported `CORE_ROLES` / `SUPPORT_ROLES` / `SAMPLER_METADATA_KEY` constants) through table-driven and looped end-to-end paths. The new tests sweep cast-history/energy combinations to confirm the canonical melody/rhythm/harmony lead with at least one support role across multiple support-role winners; sweep `(voice_count_target, max_chars, expected_size)` cases to verify clamping to `max_chars` and core-role ordering at every size; sweep preferred-synth palettes (`sw_bowed/sw_choir`, `sw_sampler/sw_bell`, `sw_drone/sw_recorder`) to confirm matching characters are promoted into the cast at `voice_count_target=5`; simulate a four-round cast-history rotation that pushes the most-recent support pick out of the next cast; drive multi-piece `assemble_cast` runs to verify piece-derived sampler-selector kwargs (`mode`, `arc_phase`, `mood`, `target_character`) propagate correctly and the sampler summary is mirrored in both the assembled entry's `sample_record` and the metadata mapping; round-trip the assembled diagnostic payload through `json.dumps` with sorted keys; and sweep selector outcomes (`sample`, `None`, `sample`) to verify `sampler_voice` always lands in the cast while `sampler_sample` metadata is attached only when the selector returns a sample. `tests/test_cast_planner_depth.py` pins the file's fractal depth at >= 2 (now `substantial (no tests)`, real_logic > trivial). Existing `test_select_cast_*`, `test_voice_count_target_*`, `test_preferred_synths_*`, and `test_sampler_*` assertions are preserved unchanged; the production `my-claw/tools/senseweave/cast_planner.py` source remains unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4409 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:669:- Added depth-2 temp sampler-dispatch planning helpers (frac-0052): root-level `temp_sampler_dispatch.py` is now import-safe outside the SenseWeave package and exposes a frozen `SamplerDispatchPlan` plus `grain_density_band`, `sampler_synth_arg_pairs`, `build_s_new_args`, `build_sampler_dispatch_plan`, and `summarize_sampler_dispatch_plan`. The helpers produce JSON-safe operator output for sample path, mode, key, buffer state, density band, key-derived or explicit transposition, gain-db-adjusted effective amp, FX preset pairs, and canonical `/s_new sw_sampler` synth args. `SamplerDispatcher.dispatch_sample` now uses the same `build_s_new_args` builder while preserving existing buffer loading, FX preset, handle-release, fire-and-forget, and sustained lifecycle behavior. `tests/test_temp_sampler_dispatch_depth.py` pins import safety, meaningful plan/summary output, end-to-end plan-to-dispatch matching, and fractal depth >= 2; production sampler dispatch tests and startup identity anchors remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:725:- Added depth-2 sampler-dispatch planning helpers (frac-0023): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/sampler_dispatch.py` now exposes a frozen `SamplerDispatchPlan` plus `grain_density_band`, `sampler_synth_arg_pairs`, `build_s_new_args`, `build_sampler_dispatch_plan`, and `summarize_sampler_dispatch_plan` so diagnostics and composer callers can inspect a concrete `sw_sampler` dispatch before or after buffer loading. The plan reports sample path, mode, key, buffer state, density band, key-derived or explicit transposition, gain-db-adjusted effective amp, FX preset pairs, and the canonical `/s_new` synth argument pairs; live `SamplerDispatcher.dispatch_sample` now uses the same `build_s_new_args` helper, preserving existing OSC ordering and lifecycle behavior. `tests/test_sampler_dispatch_depth.py` pins named density bands, loaded/unloaded plan output, JSON-safe summaries, end-to-end plan-to-dispatch matching, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_sampler_dispatch.py` and the startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
