my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:7:This PRD adds a fifth signature voice — **`sw_sampler`** — that elevates the room itself, the artist's recorded history, and a curated found-sound library into a primary instrument. The sampler is **how CypherClaw metabolizes the room**: it listens continuously to the contact mic and room mic, captures fragments worth remembering, and replays those fragments granularly — stretched, transposed, scrubbed, with a dedicated effects bus — back into the live performance.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:29:**In scope:** a granular SuperCollider voice (`sw_sampler`) with a dedicated effects bus; a sample library on disk with tag-based selection; a continuous live-capture daemon for contact/room mics; a self-quotation loop; integration with the existing artist-mode selector and cast planner so the sampler joins the signature quintet; metrics and anti-pattern detection for sampler over- or under-use.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:44:**Phase 2 — SuperCollider granular voice (CCS-009..CCS-014).** `sw_sampler.scd` SynthDef with grain-controlled buffer playback; buffer-management protocol for loading samples on demand; dedicated effects bus (delay + reverb + spectral freeze + comb-to-B); mix-engine integration so the sampler routes through the master bus. End of phase: sending OSC `/s_new sw_sampler bufnum=N grain_size=80ms density=12 pitch=0` plays a granular cloud audible through the speakers.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:58:- Existing `my-claw/tools/senseweave/synthesis/synthdefs/` directory and `boot_synthdefs.scd` — `sw_sampler.scsyndef` joins the boot-time SynthDef load.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:64:- **New** `my-claw/tools/senseweave/synthesis/synthdefs/sw_sampler.scd` source + compiled `.scsyndef`
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:71:- **Extended** `my-claw/tools/senseweave/artist_identity.py` — `SIGNATURE_VOICES = (..., "sw_sampler")`; per-mode `sampler_density` field
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:94:| CCS-006 | Add `sw_sampler` to `SIGNATURE_VOICES` quintet in `artist_identity.py` and update `VOICE_ROLES` so a `"sampler"` role maps to `"sw_sampler"`. | MUST | T1 | - `SIGNATURE_VOICES` becomes `("sw_bell_warm", "sw_bowed", "sw_breath", "sw_pad", "sw_sampler")`<br/>- `VOICE_ROLES["sampler"] = "sw_sampler"`<br/>- existing `VOICE_ROLES` keys for melody/counter/color/texture/bass unchanged<br/>- existing `test_artist_identity.py::TestSignatureVoices::test_quartet_size` is renamed to `test_quintet_size` and asserts length 5; quartet-specific assertions migrated |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:96:| CCS-008 | Register `voice_sampler` character in `character_registry.py` with `voice.synth = "sw_sampler"`, `voice.role = "sampler"`, default register, and per-mode gain overrides. | MUST | T1 | - `character_registry.py` gains `voice_sampler` entry with synth=`sw_sampler`, role=`sampler`, register=`[36, 84]`, params containing default grain_size_ms, density, pitch_transpose<br/>- character is selectable by `select_cast_ids` when `preferred_synths` includes `sw_sampler`<br/>- tests verify registration and selection through cast planner |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:97:| CCS-009 | Implement `sw_sampler.scd` granular SynthDef with bufnum, grain-size, density, position-scrub, pitch-transpose, attack/release envelope, and effects-bus send. | MUST | T1 | - SynthDef args: `bufnum`, `amp` (default 0.5), `grain_size_ms` (default 80, range 20–200), `density` (default 12 grains/sec), `position` (0..1 normalized), `position_rate` (scrub speed), `pitch_transpose_semitones` (default 0), `pitch_jitter_semitones` (default 0.1), `attack_sec` (default 0.05), `release_sec` (default 0.2), `gate` (default 1, sustained), `out_bus` (default 0), `fx_send` (default 0.4)<br/>- `doneAction:2` self-frees on envelope end<br/>- compiled `sw_sampler.scsyndef` lives in `synthesis/synthdefs/`<br/>- SC-side test (`my-claw/supercollider/test_sw_sampler.scd`) renders 2-second clip from a known buffer and verifies non-silence + spectral characteristics<br/>- gate=0 triggers release tail correctly |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:99:| CCS-011 | Implement `sampler_effects.scd` dedicated effects-bus SynthDef chain: long delay (1/4 to 1/2 measure), convolution reverb (FreeVerb fallback if no IR loaded), spectral freeze (PV_Freeze), comb-resonance tuned to B fundamental (61.74 Hz). | MUST | T1 | - SynthDef `sw_sampler_fx` reads from a stereo bus and writes to master bus<br/>- args: `delay_time` (sec, default 0.5), `delay_feedback` (0..0.85, default 0.55), `verb_mix` (default 0.35), `room_size` (default 0.7), `freeze_amount` (0..1, default 0.0), `comb_b_amount` (0..1, default 0.25), `comb_b_freq` (default 61.74)<br/>- bus number conventionally 16 (stereo, so 16+17)<br/>- compiled `sw_sampler_fx.scsyndef` lives in `synthesis/synthdefs/`<br/>- SC-side test verifies non-silent output for a known impulse input and frequency-domain check that 61.74 Hz comb peak is present when `comb_b_amount > 0` |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:100:| CCS-012 | Implement `sampler_dispatch.py` that converts a `(SampleRecord, PerformanceIntent, params)` tuple into the OSC bundle (`/s_new sw_sampler ...` + buffer-pool acquire) and ships it to scsynth. | MUST | T1 | - `dispatch_sample(record, intent, *, position, position_rate, grain_size_ms, density, pitch_transpose, amp, fx_send) -> SamplerHandle` issues `/b_allocRead` (if needed), `/s_new sw_sampler ...` and returns a handle for later `/n_set gate 0` release<br/>- correlates `record.gain_db` with `amp`<br/>- handles per-mode effects presets (delay_time / verb_mix / freeze / comb_b vary by mode)<br/>- tests with mock OSC client verify correct bundle ordering, gate-release path, and per-mode preset application |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:110:| CCS-022 | Wire `SampleSelector` into `cast_planner.select_cast_ids` so when the cast includes `sw_sampler`, a sample is pre-selected for the piece and attached to the cast metadata. | MUST | T1 | - `select_cast_ids` (or a sibling `assemble_cast`) returns cast entries with optional `sample_record: SampleRecord` field for sampler voices<br/>- selection happens once per piece commission and passes mode + arc_phase + mood + target_character (drawn from `instrument_patches.select_instrument_patch`)<br/>- tests verify sampler voices in cast carry a sample_record and that the record matches selector contracts |
