sdp/logs/Verify_T-018_20260425T183959Zc_1777169871.log:171:{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-04-26T02:23:27.444Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file_1777170207444_0","parameters":{"file_path":"sdp/verification/t-018 @20260425t183959zc-verify.md","content":"# Verification Report — T-018 @sdp/logs/Verify_T-018_20260425T183959Zc_1777169871.log\n\n**Verify Agent:** Gemini CLI\n**Date:** 2026-04-25\n**Artifacts Reviewed:**\n- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/phrase_capture.py`\n- `tests/test_phrase_capture.py`\n- `ESCALATIONS.md`\n\n## Correctness\nThe implementation of sample tagging metadata is correct and matches the requirements. Each captured phrase is now accompanied by a sidecar `.json` file containing the mandatory tags: `instrument`, `song_id`, `key`, `tempo`, `timestamp`, `duration`, and `source`. The schema validation logic ensures that all required keys are present and have the correct types.\n\n## Completeness\nThe task is complete. All specified metadata fields are included in the sidecar JSON. The `PhraseCaptureWriter` handles both MIDI (`keyboard`) and Audio (`theramini`) sources. Edge cases, such as sub-threshold bursts that do not result in a written sample, are correctly handled by not writing a sidecar file.\n\n## Consistency\nThe code follows the project's established patterns, utilizing `pathlib` for file operations and `json` for metadata serialization. The metadata fields and their naming conventions are consistent with the provided specification.\n\n## Security\nNo security vulnerabilities were identified. The use of UUID-based suffixes for filenames prevents collisions, and the sidecar files are stored securely alongside the audio/MIDI assets.\n\n## Quality\nThe implementation is high-quality, with clean separation of concerns between capturing, validating, and persisting metadata. The tests in `tests/test_phrase_capture.py` are comprehensive, covering schema validation, default values, user-supplied tags, and path pairing.\n\n## Issues Found\n- [ ] [Issue — severity: minor] `PhraseCaptureWriter` is not yet integrated into `midi_keyboard_listener.py` or `theramini_listener.py`. This is known and expected to be addressed in the final subtask (Zd).\n\n## Verdict: PASS\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\nExcellent implementation of the metadata sidecar logic. The schema validator is robust and the tests are thorough. Ready for integration into the listeners in the next phase.\n"}}
sdp/logs/Verify_T-018_20260425T183959Zc_1777169871.log:186:{"type":"tool_result","timestamp":"2026-04-26T02:23:37.657Z","tool_id":"run_shell_command_1777170217313_0","status":"success","output":"commit 45324813b64ba6313d17f6bc5413d0f15e8f4a9a\nAuthor: Anthony Ainsworth <anthony@cascadiantech.com>\nDate:   Sat Apr 25 19:17:11 2026 -0700\n\n    feat(capture): write sample tagging metadata sidecar JSON [T-018@20260425T183959Zc]\n    \n    Each captured phrase now persists a sidecar `<sample>.json` file alongside\n    the audio/MIDI artifact with the full tag set: instrument, song_id, key,\n    tempo, timestamp, duration, source.\n    \n    PhraseCaptureWriter accepts an optional `metadata` mapping at construction\n    and exposes `set_metadata(...)` for per-phrase context updates. Derived\n    fields (timestamp, duration) are always computed from the phrase boundary\n    and cannot be overridden. `instrument` defaults to the capture source and\n    `source` defaults to \"human\".\n    \n    A SAMPLE_METADATA_SCHEMA constant plus a `validate_sample_metadata` helper\n    guard payload completeness and types; the writer self-validates on every\n    emit. Tests cover defaults, custom tags, derived-field rejection, schema\n    errors, and timestamp/duration accuracy.\n    \n    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>\n\n my-claw/tools/senseweave/phrase_capture.py |  86 ++++++++++++-\n tests/test_phrase_capture.py               | 200 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++-\n 2 files changed, 284 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)"}

