sdp/verification/t-020@20260416t043834z-verify.md:8:The new arrangement engine defines lane events, register bands, density gates, and automation curves and is fully exercised by dedicated tests. `build_arrangement_plan()` now returns per-scene timelines plus automation overrides, and automated tests cover sparse/medium/full lane counts, staged entry, doubles/dropouts, thinning behavior, register safety, and non-flat automation. 1975 tests pass with `pip install -e '.[dev]' && pytest tests/ -x`.
sdp/verification/t-020@20260416t043834z-verify.md:11:The feature is well covered at the arrangement-model level, including staged-growth and thinning guarantees. However, the time-based timeline from `ArrangementTimeline` is not yet consumed in tracker lane-role orchestration: `my-claw/tools/senseweave/music_tracker.py` currently uses only `automation_overrides`/`entry_intent` from `ArrangementScenePlan`, and does not act on `lane_events` or timeline role/actions.
sdp/verification/frac-0082-verify.md:31:The E2E class covers the full one-path pipeline: profile lookup → entrainment nudge → IOI pair (even/odd) → meter-policy overlay → JSON-safe metadata → tracker scene compilation with role-based lane offsets. All seven fields named in the spec's scene-preservation requirement (`groove_identity`, `meter/subdivision policy`, `swing ratio`, `breath/polyrhythm metadata`, `lane-level timing offsets`, `positive row lengths`) are asserted in `test_tracker_scene_uses_profile_offsets_and_arc_meter_policy`. The depth gate is pinned via AST parse and `sdp.fractal.classify_depth`, satisfying the structural requirement without runtime import side effects.
sdp/verification/t-019@20260416t043834z-verify.md:10:- Tracker scene building now stamps groove metadata onto `TrackerScene.metadata` and each `TrackerStep.metadata`.
sdp/verification/t-032-verify.md:22:3. **Typed upload helper** — `audio_streamer.py` exposes `build_segment_upload_request`, `post_segment_to_worker`, and `SegmentUploadResult`. `test_post_segment_to_worker_sends_streamer_headers_and_reports_latency` passes and asserts all canonical headers: `Authorization`, `Content-Type`, `X-CypherClaw-Sequence`, `X-CypherClaw-Captured-At`, `X-CypherClaw-Duration`, `X-CypherClaw-Scene`, `X-CypherClaw-Tuning`, `X-CypherClaw-Source`, plus `latency_ms` parsing from the Worker response. ✓
